Compile the code using command:

>> javac Restaurant.java

Run the program using command :

>> java Restaurant <input_filename>

To write the output to a file use command :

>> java Restaurant <input_filename> > <output_filename>




For the simulation 1 minute is taken as 0.1 s.
2 minutes as 0.2 s and so on..
Output time unit is minutes.


If the time at which tables are allocated seems to be off by a couple of minutes do the following:

In Restaurant.java, main method, variable timeunit is assigned value 100. Increase this value to 200. If its still wrong further increase to a higher value. 


